dh90Type.name: dh90Type
dh90Type.description: Identifies the type of Hub defined and identifies standalone configurations managed by DECagent 90 modules. Setting this variable to invalid deletes the community associated with the community string and releases the RAM and flash memory resources used by the community.

dh90LastChange.name: dh90LastChange
dh90LastChange.description: The value of the sysUpTime at the time this hub added or removed a module.

dh90NumberSlots.name: dh90NumberSlots
dh90NumberSlots.description: Number of slots in backplane. Setting this variable to values of 1, 8 or 16 defines the size of a hub in a particular community.

dh90SlotTable.name: dh90SlotTable
dh90SlotTable.description: A list of modules installed in the DEChub 90. The number of entries is given in dh90SlotNumber. To create a new row (module) in the slot table, set a EMPTY dh90SlotModuleType to the appropriate value. If adding a bridge or server, next set the dh90SlotPhysicalAddress for the row. Sets of the other variables in the row must be done in separate PDUs AFTER the mac address of the device has been set correctly.

dh90SlotEntry.name: dh90SlotEntry
dh90SlotEntry.description: Contains objects defining characteristics of modules in the DEChub 90

dh90SlotIndex.name: dh90SlotIndex
dh90SlotIndex.description: The slot number containing the module

dh90SlotModuleType.name: dh90SlotModuleType
dh90SlotModuleType.description: The type of the module in a slot. If the slot is known to be empty, a value of empty is used. If the slot is occupied by a module of unknown type, a value of unknown is used.

dh90SlotModuleName.name: dh90SlotModuleName
dh90SlotModuleName.description: A textual description of the module

dh90SlotModuleVersion.name: dh90SlotModuleVersion
dh90SlotModuleVersion.description: A textual description of the version level of the hardware and firmware of the module

dh90SlotCounterTime.name: dh90SlotCounterTime
dh90SlotCounterTime.description: Time since the counters of this module were zeroed

dh90SlotIfBase.name: dh90SlotIfBase
dh90SlotIfBase.description: An index into the ifTable for the first interface on this module. Add one to this value to reference the ifTable entry which corresponds to the second interface, etc. If no interface(s) is/are supported on the module, a value of zero is returned.

dh90SlotIfNumber.name: dh90SlotIfNumber
dh90SlotIfNumber.description: Number of interfaces on this module.

dh90SlotPhysicalAddress.name: dh90SlotPhysicalAddress
dh90SlotPhysicalAddress.description: A read-write variable for the physical address to allow devices to be added to the hub remotely. Writing this variable as part of a remote add device routine will cause the new physical address to be accessable in the corresponding ifPhysAddress variable in ifTable.

dh90SlotNumberOfPorts.name: dh90SlotNumberOfPorts
dh90SlotNumberOfPorts.description: The number of ports on this module. Returns 8 for DECserver90L and DECrepeater90T, 6 for DECrepeater90C.

dh90SlotPassword.name: dh90SlotPassword
dh90SlotPassword.description: Password used to enable privileged operations on the DECserver90L and access to the bridge. Reads to this variable will return a null string.

dh90SlotNewPassword.name: dh90SlotNewPassword
dh90SlotNewPassword.description: Setting this variable causes the agent to set a new password on the terminal server using the TSNewPassword value as the new password and TSPassword as the old password. Power on the terminal server must be cycled within a minute for the change to take effect. Reads to this variable will return a null string.

dh90SlotPolling.name: dh90SlotPolling
dh90SlotPolling.description: The current polling status of the module. If the DECagent 90 is polling this device, a get of this variable will return 'on', otherwise 'off' is returned. Setting this variable to 'off' causes the agent to stop polling the device in this slot. Setting this variable to 'on' causes the agent to start polling the device in the specified slot. If a device does not repond to a poll, an moduleDown enterprise specific trap is generated.

dh90SlotPrimarySpecific.name: dh90SlotPrimarySpecific
dh90SlotPrimarySpecific.description: A reference to the Bridge { experimental 14 }, the Character-like { experimental 19 } or the { drpt90 } repeater portion of this MIB definition. If the module realizes some other function, the object identifier nullSpecific OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is returned.

dh90SlotSecondarySpecific.name: dh90SlotSecondarySpecific
dh90SlotSecondarySpecific.description: A reference to the RS232-like { experimental 20 } MIB definition, if dh90ModulePrimarySpecific identifies the Character-like MIB. Otherwise, the object identifier nullSpecific OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { 0 0 } is returned.

dh90TrapAddressTable.name: dh90TrapAddressTable
dh90TrapAddressTable.description: A table of IP Addresses to which this device will send traps.

dh90TrapEntry.name: dh90TrapEntry
dh90TrapEntry.description: Each entry contains an IP Address to which all SNMP Traps will be sent by this community.

dh90TrapAddress.name: dh90TrapAddress
dh90TrapAddress.description: An IP Address to which all SNMP traps generated by this device will be sent. Setting a instance to a value of zero will delete the row in the table.

da90FlashErasures.name: da90FlashErasures
da90FlashErasures.description: The number of times the flash memory on this DECagent 90 has been erased. This number is the total of erasures for all segments of flash.

da90Maintenance.name: da90Maintenance
da90Maintenance.description: A control variable to reset the counters on a DECagent 90. In response to a get-request or a get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready'. Setting the value to 'reset' causes the entire module to be reset. Setting the value to 'resetToFactory' causes the entire device to be reset to the original factory settings.

da90CommunityNumber.name: da90CommunityNumber
da90CommunityNumber.description: Number of community string-pair entries in da90HubCommStrsTable.

da90CommunityTable.name: da90CommunityTable
da90CommunityTable.description: A table of community string pairs for client hubs.

da90CommunityEntry.name: da90CommunityEntry
da90CommunityEntry.description: Contains a pair of community strings, one specifying a read-only profile, the other a read-write profile.

da90CommunityIndex.name: da90CommunityIndex
da90CommunityIndex.description: Index into hub community string pair table, identifies the community being accessed

da90CommunityType.name: da90CommunityType
da90CommunityType.description: Identifies whether the current community information in the DENMA is active for this row in the community table. Setting to invalid frees the NVRAM used to store the community information (destroys the slot table and port tables for this community).

da90CommunityROString.name: da90CommunityROString
da90CommunityROString.description: Community string, with a read-only profile, used to access a da90's client Hub. All community strings in the read-only set must be unique. Setting such a community string to a pre-existing value returns a status of BadValue. Reading this variable with any community string other than the agent's community string will return a zero length string.

da90CommunityRWString.name: da90CommunityRWString
da90CommunityRWString.description: Community string, with a read-write profile, used to access a da90's client Hub. All community strings in the read-only set must be unique. Setting such a community string to a pre-existing value returns a status of BadValue. Reading this variable with any community string other than the agent's read-write community string will return a zero length string.

da90CommunityTrapString.name: da90CommunityTrapString
da90CommunityTrapString.description: Community string sent with traps generated due to events caused by this community. The trap community strings do not have to be unique. This variable is read using the agent's community string.

ds90LNumberModules.name: ds90LNumberModules
ds90LNumberModules.description: Number of DECserver 90L Modules represented in the ds90LModuleTable.

ds90LModuleTable.name: ds90LModuleTable
ds90LModuleTable.description: A table of DECserver 90L modules installed in the group. The number of entries is given in ds90LModuleNumber.

ds90LModuleEntry.name: ds90LModuleEntry
ds90LModuleEntry.description: Contains objects defining characteristics of DECserver 90L modules in the group

ds90LSlotIndex.name: ds90LSlotIndex
ds90LSlotIndex.description: The slot index value which addresses the dh90SlotTable for this module.

ds90LDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.name: ds90LDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions
ds90LDot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt on a particular interface is delayed because the medium is busy. The count represented by an instance of this object does not include frames involved in collisions.

ds90LDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.name: ds90LDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames
ds90LDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. (If DS90L is implementing the MIB-II if group, the following also applies: A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts or ifOutNUcastPkts object and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the ds90LDot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames object.)

ds90LDot3StatsMultipleCollsionFrames.name: ds90LDot3StatsMultipleCollsionFrames
ds90LDot3StatsMultipleCollsionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. (If DS90L is implementing the MIB-II if group, the following also applies: A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts or ifOutNUcastPkts object and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the ds90LDot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames object.)

ds90LEnetDataOverruns.name: ds90LEnetDataOverruns
ds90LEnetDataOverruns.description: A count of the number of frames arriving at the DS90L lost due to data overrun since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatCircMsgsIns.name: ds90LLatCircMsgsIns
ds90LLatCircMsgsIns.description: A count of the number of LAT circuit messages received by this DS90L since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatCircMsgsOuts.name: ds90LLatCircMsgsOuts
ds90LLatCircMsgsOuts.description: A count of the number of LAT circuit messages transmitted by this DS90L since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatSessSolicitAccepts.name: ds90LLatSessSolicitAccepts
ds90LLatSessSolicitAccepts.description: A count of the number of LAT Solicits accepted by this DS90L since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatSessSolicitRejects.name: ds90LLatSessSolicitRejects
ds90LLatSessSolicitRejects.description: A count of the number of LAT Solicits rejected by this DS90L since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatCircDuplsMsgs.name: ds90LLatCircDuplsMsgs
ds90LLatCircDuplsMsgs.description: A count of the number of duplicate LAT messages the DS90L LAT implementation has discarded since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatCircMsgRetransmits.name: ds90LLatCircMsgRetransmits
ds90LLatCircMsgRetransmits.description: A count of the total number of LAT circuit messages this DS90L has retransmitted since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatSessIllegalSlots.name: ds90LLatSessIllegalSlots
ds90LLatSessIllegalSlots.description: A count of the number of illegal LAT slots the DS90L has received on all LAT sessions since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LIllegalMulticastRcvs.name: ds90LIllegalMulticastRcvs
ds90LIllegalMulticastRcvs.description: This counts the number of illegal multicast LAT messages received on this DECserver 90L since it last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LLatCircKeepAlive.name: ds90LLatCircKeepAlive
ds90LLatCircKeepAlive.description: This defines the number of seconds the LAT circuits provider waits between transmitting LAT circuit layer keep-alive messages. Writing to this object is equivalent to issuing the CHANGE SERVER KEEPALIVE TIMER command via the user interface.

ds90LLatCircRetransmitLimit.name: ds90LLatCircRetransmitLimit
ds90LLatCircRetransmitLimit.description: This object defines the maximum number of LAT circuit message retransmissions the server will attempt before declaring the circuit failed. Writing to this object is equivalent to issuing the CHANGE SERVER RETRANSMIT LIMIT command via the user interface.

ds90LLatCircInvalidMsgs.name: ds90LLatCircInvalidMsgs
ds90LLatCircInvalidMsgs.description: This counts the number of invalid LAT messages received on its entry's LAT circuit since the DECserver90L last reinitialized or zeroed counters.

ds90LAuthorizeMode.name: ds90LAuthorizeMode
ds90LAuthorizeMode.description: Setting this value to enable causes the SET A,password command to be sent to the DECserver 90. The module will enter authorized mode IF the power is cycled on the module within one minute. The password used will be the current value of dh90ModulePassword. Setting this variable to disable results in authorized mode being cleared

ds90LMaintenance.name: ds90LMaintenance
ds90LMaintenance.description: A control variable to reset the counters on a DECserver 90L. In response to a get-request or a get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready'. Setting the value to 'zeroCounters' causes the if, LAT and dh90SlotCounterTime counters to be cleared. Setting the value to 'reset' causes the entire module to be reset, any users and circuits will be disconnected. Setting the value to 'resetToFactory' causes the entire device to be reset to the original factory settings. Passwords, port names and printer speeds will be cleared.

ds90LPrompt.name: ds90LPrompt
ds90LPrompt.description: A DECserver 90L+ (PLUS) variable. Contains the prompt displayed when a session is local to the PLUS version of the terminal server. The default value is '->'. This variable is not present if the server is a DECserver 90L.

ds90LPortTable.name: ds90LPortTable
ds90LPortTable.description: Table of port specific variables on this DECserver90L.

ds90LPortIndex.name: ds90LPortIndex
ds90LPortIndex.description: The value of charPortIndex for this port.

ds90LPortRemoteModification.name: ds90LPortRemoteModification
ds90LPortRemoteModification.description: Enables and disables remote modification of of the port by the host system.

ds90LPortType.name: ds90LPortType
ds90LPortType.description: Selects the type of device connected to the port.

ds90LPortBreak.name: ds90LPortBreak
ds90LPortBreak.description: Determines if the port responds to local or remote break.

ds90LPortTest.name: ds90LPortTest
ds90LPortTest.description: Setting this variable to enable places the port into loopback mode. Loopback mode can be used to verify that a port is receiving and sending characters.

ds90LPortAutoConfigure.name: ds90LPortAutoConfigure
ds90LPortAutoConfigure.description: A DECserver 90L+ (PLUS) variable. Enables or disables the Autoconfiguration of the port, the ability of the port to autobaud. Disabling autoconfiguration also causes the speed and characteristics of the port to be stored in non-volatile memory on the server. The variable is not present if the server is a DECserver 90L.

ds90LPortOnDemandLoading.name: ds90LPortOnDemandLoading
ds90LPortOnDemandLoading.description: A DECserver 90L+ (PLUS) variable. Enables or disables on demand loading of fonts. The variable is not present if the server is a DECserver 90L.

ds90LSessionTable.name: ds90LSessionTable
ds90LSessionTable.description: The list of all LAT sessions active on this DECserver90L.

ds90LPortEntry.name: ds90LPortEntry
ds90LPortEntry.description: A single LAT session instance this DS90L currently provides.

ds90LSessionEntry.name: ds90LSessionEntry
ds90LSessionEntry.description: A single LAT session instance this DS90L currently provides.

ds90LSessionPort.name: ds90LSessionPort
ds90LSessionPort.description: The value of charPortIndex for the port to which this session belongs.

ds90LSessionIndex.name: ds90LSessionIndex
ds90LSessionIndex.description: The session index in the context of the port, a non-zero positive integer. Will be 1 for the DECserver90L, 4 for DECserver 90L+.

ds90LSessionRemoteNode.name: ds90LSessionRemoteNode
ds90LSessionRemoteNode.description: The name of the remote node providing the service for this session.

ds90LSessionService.name: ds90LSessionService
ds90LSessionService.description: The service to which this session is connected.

ds90LSessionRemotePortId.name: ds90LSessionRemotePortId
ds90LSessionRemotePortId.description: The name of the port at the remote node providing the connection, for instance LAT121.

drpt90PortTable.name: drpt90PortTable
drpt90PortTable.description: A list of port entries. The index for a repeater port is given by (slot number*100) + port number The number of ports is given by dh90SlotTable.dh90SlotEntry. dh90SlotNumberOfPorts.

drpt90PortEntry.name: drpt90PortEntry
drpt90PortEntry.description: A collection of objects containing information for a given interface.

drpt90PortIndex.name: drpt90PortIndex
drpt90PortIndex.description: Identifies the module and port. The value of this object is given by: (slot number*100) + port number

drpt90PortName.name: drpt90PortName
drpt90PortName.description: The text description of the port given by management

drpt90PortAdminStatus.name: drpt90PortAdminStatus
drpt90PortAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the port.

drpt90PortState.name: drpt90PortState
drpt90PortState.description: The state of the port. Unknown(1) is returned when the port state cannot be determined. AutoPartitioned(2) indicates that the repeater has disabled the port automatically, ManagementPartitioned(3) indicates that the port has been disabled remotely, and active(4) indicates that the port is operational.

drpt90PortType.name: drpt90PortType
drpt90PortType.description: The Physical Medium type of the port

drpt90PortPartitionCount.name: drpt90PortPartitionCount
drpt90PortPartitionCount.description: The number of times this port has partitioned. This value is only significant if drpt90PortStatus is not unknown(1).

drpt90PortAutoPartitionReason.name: drpt90PortAutoPartitionReason
drpt90PortAutoPartitionReason.description: Errors currently detected on the port.

drpt90PortJamBits.name: drpt90PortJamBits
drpt90PortJamBits.description: The number of jam bits being used on the port segment.

drpt90PortAddrTable.name: drpt90PortAddrTable
drpt90PortAddrTable.description: A list of MAC addresses paired with the repeater port on which they have been seen.

drpt90PortAddrEntry.name: drpt90PortAddrEntry
drpt90PortAddrEntry.description: A MAC addresses and the repeater port on which it resides.

drpt90PortPhyAddr.name: drpt90PortPhyAddr
drpt90PortPhyAddr.description: A MAC address seen on this port

drpt90PortAddrIndex.name: drpt90PortAddrIndex
drpt90PortAddrIndex.description: Identifies the module and port. The value of this object the same as drpt90PortIndex and is given by: (slot number*100) + port number

dbSysRomVersion.name: dbSysRomVersion
dbSysRomVersion.description: The version number of the software stored in ROM.

dbSysInitSwitch.name: dbSysInitSwitch
dbSysInitSwitch.description: This object allows the management action of initializing a device and forcing it to run selftest. It can also be used to reset all information added to the device's NVRAM. When read, it returns a value of other(1). When set to a value of 'reset', the bridge will empty the forwarding data base and start relearning. When set to 'resetToFactory', the bridge will empty the forwarding data base, reset spanning tree and clear all protocol filters and password.

dbSysDeviceState.name: dbSysDeviceState
dbSysDeviceState.description: The operational state of the device.

dbSysNvramFailed.name: dbSysNvramFailed
dbSysNvramFailed.description: A flag, that, when set to True, indicates that the NVRAM failed selftest following the last initialization of the device. Values set to variables maintained on the bridge will not be preserved over a power cycle of the bridge.

dbIfTable.name: dbIfTable
dbIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by ifNumber, defined in [2].

dbIfEntry.name: dbIfEntry
dbIfEntry.description: A collection of objects containing information for a given interface.

dbIfIndex.name: dbIfIndex
dbIfIndex.description: Identifies the Interface. The value of this the same object is as the ifIndex, defined in [2], for this interface.

dbIfBadFramesReceived.name: dbIfBadFramesReceived
dbIfBadFramesReceived.description: Number of frames received with a bad frame check sequence or the device received a frame loss indication from the hardware on the interface.

dbIfTransmitFramesError.name: dbIfTransmitFramesError
dbIfTransmitFramesError.description: Number of frames that were transmitted with an error on the line.

db90LB100SpanningTreeVer.name: db90LB100SpanningTreeVer
db90LB100SpanningTreeVer.description: The version number of the Spanning Tree algorithm used by the bridge when in the LAN Bridge 100 Spanning Tree mode.

db90802SpanningTreeVer.name: db90802SpanningTreeVer
db90802SpanningTreeVer.description: The version number of the Spanning Tree algorithm used by the bridge when in the 802.1d Spanning Tree mode.

db90MaxForwardingDBEntries.name: db90MaxForwardingDBEntries
db90MaxForwardingDBEntries.description: The maximum number of address entries that the bridge can store in its volatile memory.

db90MaxNVForwardingDBEntries.name: db90MaxNVForwardingDBEntries
db90MaxNVForwardingDBEntries.description: The maximum number of permanent address entries that the bridge can store in its NVRAM.

db90MaxProtocolDBEntries.name: db90MaxProtocolDBEntries
db90MaxProtocolDBEntries.description: The maximum number of protocol entries that the bridge can store in its protocol database. These entries control the handling of frames based on their Ethernet PT, IEEE 802.2 DSAP or IEEE 802 SNAP Protocol ID.

db90MaxNVProtocolDBEntries.name: db90MaxNVProtocolDBEntries
db90MaxNVProtocolDBEntries.description: The maximum number of protocol entries that the bridge can store in its nonvolatile memory. These are retained after a power-down.

db90CurrProtocolDBEntries.name: db90CurrProtocolDBEntries
db90CurrProtocolDBEntries.description: The number of protocol entries that are stored in the bridge's protocol database. These control the handling of frames based on their Ethernet protocol type, IEEE 802.2 DSAP, or 802 SNAP Protocol ID.

db90CurrNVProtocolDBEntries.name: db90CurrNVProtocolDBEntries
db90CurrNVProtocolDBEntries.description: The number of protocol entries in the bridge's NVRAM. These are retained after a power loss.

db90MgmtHeardPort.name: db90MgmtHeardPort
db90MgmtHeardPort.description: The port on which this command was received.

db90LB100BeingPolled.name: db90LB100BeingPolled
db90LB100BeingPolled.description: The address of the LAN Bridge 100 mode bridge that sent this bridge into the LAN Bridge 100 Spanning Tree mode. If this bridge is the Root, this object indicates the bridge that will be polled periodically to determine if it is still necessary to stay in this Spanning Tree mode.

db90TimeSinceLastHello.name: db90TimeSinceLastHello
db90TimeSinceLastHello.description: The number of seconds since the bridge last sent a Hello message.

db90HubManagement.name: db90HubManagement
db90HubManagement.description: Indicates whether the bridge is managing the hub (i.e., is capable of managing repeaters inserted in the hub).

db90CurrFdbEntries.name: db90CurrFdbEntries
db90CurrFdbEntries.description: The number of entries currently active in the DECbridge 90 forwarding data base, or one more than the value of db90MaxForwardingDBEntries if the bridge has exceededd the size of the forwarding data base hardware.

db90SpanningTreeModeChanges.name: db90SpanningTreeModeChanges
db90SpanningTreeModeChanges.description: The number of times that the bridge switched from the 802.1d Spanning Tree mode to the LB100 Spanning Tree mode.

db90BestRootAge.name: db90BestRootAge
db90BestRootAge.description: The age, in hundredths of seconds, of the Hello message that established the best root.

db90TopologyChangeFlag.name: db90TopologyChangeFlag
db90TopologyChangeFlag.description: A flag that indicates whether a Topology Change is currently in effect on the extended LAN.

db90TellParentFlag.name: db90TellParentFlag
db90TellParentFlag.description: A flag that indicates if the bridge is attempting to propagate a topology change towards the Root.

db90ForwardingDBShortAgingTime.name: db90ForwardingDBShortAgingTime
db90ForwardingDBShortAgingTime.description: The number of seconds that the bridge keeps learned entries active while a topology change is in effect.

db90BadHelloLimit.name: db90BadHelloLimit
db90BadHelloLimit.description: The number of hello intervals during which the bridge receives one or more bad hellos on a line, before the bridge performs a test on the link. A bad Hello message is one that contains inferior information that is received on a port on which this bridge is Designated.

db90BadHelloResetTimer.name: db90BadHelloResetTimer
db90BadHelloResetTimer.description: The number of Hello intervals without bad Hellos that the bridge will wait before it resets its bad Hello count to zero.

db90NoFrameInterval.name: db90NoFrameInterval
db90NoFrameInterval.description: The The number of seconds of inactivity on a line that will cause the bridge to run a test on that line. The bridge considers a line to be inactive if it does not receive any frames on that line.

db90LB100PollTime.name: db90LB100PollTime
db90LB100PollTime.description: The number of seconds that a Root bridge in LAN Bridge 100 mode waits between polling the LAN Bridge 100 that is keeping it in this mode. This polling is done to determine whether the LB100 is still present on the extended LAN.

db90LB100ResponseTimeout.name: db90LB100ResponseTimeout
db90LB100ResponseTimeout.description: The number of seconds that a Root in LAN Bridge 100 Spanning Tree mode will wait for a response from the LAN Bridge 100 which is keeping it in this mode, before which it will assume that the LB100 is no longer on the extended LAN.

db90LB100SpanningTreeCompat.name: db90LB100SpanningTreeCompat
db90LB100SpanningTreeCompat.description: A switch that controls the Spanning Tree mode used by the bridge. If in Auto-Select mode, the bridge will go into 802 Spanning Tree mode by default, but will switch to LB100 mode as soon as a LB100 is detected. In 802 Spanning Tree mode, the bridge will stay in 802 mode.

db90IfTable.name: db90IfTable
db90IfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by ifNumber, defined in [2].

db90IfEntry.name: db90IfEntry
db90IfEntry.description: A collection of objects containing information for a given interface.

db90IfIndex.name: db90IfIndex
db90IfIndex.description: Identifies the Interface. The value of this object is the same as the ifIndex, defined in [2], for this interface.

db90IfDeviceFramesReceived.name: db90IfDeviceFramesReceived
db90IfDeviceFramesReceived.description: The number of frames addressed to the bridge itself that were received on this line.

db90IfBadHelloLimitExceeded.name: db90IfBadHelloLimitExceeded
db90IfBadHelloLimitExceeded.description: The number of times that the Bad Hellos on the line exceeded the Bad Hello limit.

db90IfEtherTable.name: db90IfEtherTable
db90IfEtherTable.description: A list of interface entries for an Ethernet port.

db90IfEtherEntry.name: db90IfEtherEntry
db90IfEtherEntry.description: A collection of objects containing information for a given interface.

db90IfEthIndex.name: db90IfEthIndex
db90IfEthIndex.description: Identifies the Interface. The value of this object is the same as the ifIndex, defined in [2], for this interface.

db90IfEthFramingError.name: db90IfEthFramingError
db90IfEthFramingError.description: The number of times that a frame received on the line contained both a noninteger multiple of 8 bits and a CRC error.

db90IfEthCarrierLoss.name: db90IfEthCarrierLoss
db90IfEthCarrierLoss.description: The number of times that the bridge detected a loss of the carrier signal while transmitting a frame on the line.

db90IfEthCollisionLimitExceeded.name: db90IfEthCollisionLimitExceeded
db90IfEthCollisionLimitExceeded.description: The number of times that the bridge failed to transmit a frame on this line after 16 attempts, the collision limit.

db90IfSpanTable.name: db90IfSpanTable
db90IfSpanTable.description: A list of interface entries for a port.

db90IfSpanEntry.name: db90IfSpanEntry
db90IfSpanEntry.description: A collection of objects containing information for a given interface.

db90IfSpIndex.name: db90IfSpIndex
db90IfSpIndex.description: Identifies the Interface. The value of this object is the same as the ifIndex, defined in [2], for this interface.

db90IfSpDesigRootAge.name: db90IfSpDesigRootAge
db90IfSpDesigRootAge.description: The age, in hundreths of seconds, of the last Hello message received from the designated bridge on the line.

db90IfSpForwardDelayTimer.name: db90IfSpForwardDelayTimer
db90IfSpForwardDelayTimer.description: The time remaining, in hundreths of seconds, before the bridge will leave the Learning State of Preforwarding, and enter the Forwarding State.

db90IfSpBadHelloCount.name: db90IfSpBadHelloCount
db90IfSpBadHelloCount.description: The number of Hello intervals during which at least one Bad Hello was received.

db90IfSpTopologyChangeAckFlag.name: db90IfSpTopologyChangeAckFlag
db90IfSpTopologyChangeAckFlag.description: A flag that indicates whether a topology change notification received on a link that we are designated on needs to be acknowledged.

db90ProtoFilterOther.name: db90ProtoFilterOther
db90ProtoFilterOther.description: Action taken by the bridge on Ethernet protocol types or the 5-byte SNAP PIDs other than those specified in the db90ProtoTable. This value defaults to forward(1) and is modified only if a protocol with db90filterEntry.db90FilterStatus of forward(1) is entered into the table.

db90ProtoFilterTable.name: db90ProtoFilterTable
db90ProtoFilterTable.description: A table that contains filtering information about Ethernet protocol types and 5 byte SNAP PIDs for the DECbridge 90.

db90ProtoFilterEntry.name: db90ProtoFilterEntry
db90ProtoFilterEntry.description: A table that contains filtering characteristics for Ethernet protocol types and 5 byte SNAP PIDs for the DECbridge 90.

db90ProtoFilterProtocol.name: db90ProtoFilterProtocol
db90ProtoFilterProtocol.description: The protocol type or SNAP PID in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies. The length is 2 for Ethernet protocol types and 5 for SNAP PID.

db90ProtoFilterType.name: db90ProtoFilterType
db90ProtoFilterType.description: The type of this entry. unknown(1) specifies that this protocol filter is unused. invalid(2) deletes the filter. ethernet(3) or snap-sap(4) defines the size of db90ProtoFilterProtocol.

db90ProtoFilterStatus.name: db90ProtoFilterStatus
db90ProtoFilterStatus.description: Action taken by bridge when it sees this ethernet protocol type or SNAP PID in a received frame. Note that this value must be identical to db90ProtoFilterOther unless db90ProtoFilterMulticastFlag is multicastOnly(2) or there are no other entries with db90ProtoFilterMulticastFlag=allFrames(1).

db90ProtoFilterMulticastFlag.name: db90ProtoFilterMulticastFlag
db90ProtoFilterMulticastFlag.description: Identifies whether or not filtering is based on the multicast bit in the MAC destination address. If allFrames(1), then filtering is performed as per db90ProtoFilterStatus. For multicastOnly(2), multicast frames for this protocol are always filtered and unicast frames are always forwarded; this is true regardless of the value of db90ProtoFilterOther.

db90ProtoFilterPortMask.name: db90ProtoFilterPortMask
db90ProtoFilterPortMask.description: Must be allPorts(3) unless db90ProtoFilterMulticastFlag is multicastOnly, in which case any specification is valid.
